title: Appointments to Social Welfare Advisory Committee
content_text:
p>
The Government today (December 1) announced the appointment of four new members 
and the re-appointment of the chairman and seven incumbent members to the Social 
Welfare Advisory Committee (SWAC). All appointments are for two years with 
effect from today.  The four new members are: Mr Bunny Chan Chung-bun, Mr Kwan Chuk-fai, Dr Lam 
Ching-choi and Dr Leung Wing-tai. Mr Chan is Chairman of the Kwun Tong District Council and a member of the

Commission on Youth and the Commission on Strategic Development. He was also the 
Chairman of Pok Oi Hospital in 2003-04. Mr Chan has worked in close co-operation 
with the Social Welfare Department on various policies and initiatives. Mr Kwan is the General Manager (Corporate Communication) of NWS Holdings Ltd. He 
is currently a member of the Community Investment and Inclusion Fund Committee 
and has experience working with the welfare sector. Dr Lam is the Chief Executive Officer of the Haven of Hope Christian Service, a

subvented non-governmental organisation (NGO) with a joint focus on welfare and 
health services. He is also a member of the Elderly Commission and the Community 
Investment and Inclusion Fund Committee. Dr Leung is the Chief Secretary General of Breakthrough Limited which is a non-subvented 
NGO. He is also a council member of two local universities with strong 
commitment to youth work in Hong Kong. He was also a member of the former Board

commitment to youth work in Hong Kong. He was also a member of the former Board 
of Education and the Assessment Sub-Committee of the Quality Education Fund. Meanwhile, the Chairman and seven incumbent members have been re-appointed. They 
are: Mr Wilfred Wong Ying-wai, Dr Stephen Chow Chun-kay, Mr Quentin Fong 
King-sang, Mr Herman Hui Chung-shing, Dr Benjamin Lai Sau-shun, Mr Vincent Lo

Wing-sang, Mr Tung Chi-fat, and Ms Lisa Yip Sau-wah. The Secretary for Health, Welfare and Food, Dr York Chow, welcomed the 
appointment of the new members and the re-appointment of the chairman and 
incumbent members. He looked forward to their contribution to the development of 
welfare policy issues. Dr Chow also thanked the two outgoing members �V Mrs Cheung Ang Siew-mei; and Mr 
Keith Lam Hon-keung - for their valuable advice to the SWAC during their term of

appointment. The functions of the SWAC are to keep social welfare services under continuous review, and to advise the Government on all matters of social welfare policy. Following is the membership list of the SWAC as from December 1, 2006: Chairman:
